# No Markdown or Symbols in Spoken Text — ABSOLUTE BAN

Every string passed to `oc-speak.sh` (ack, thinking, status, completion, question — every session type) must be **plain spoken English**. The TTS engine reads characters literally, so raw markup sounds broken.

## Banned characters and patterns — never include these in TTS text

| Banned | Why it sounds bad | Say instead |
|--------|-------------------|-------------|
| `**word**` or `*word*` | Reads "asterisk asterisk word asterisk asterisk" | Just say the word with no wrapping |
| `__word__` | Reads "underscore underscore" | Just say the word |
| `` `code` `` | Reads "backtick code backtick" | Say the word or describe it conversationally |
| `# Heading` | Reads "hash heading" | Just say the heading text |
| `- bullet` | Reads "dash bullet" | Say the item naturally in a sentence |
| `[label](url)` | Reads the raw bracket/parenthesis soup | Say the label or describe the link |
| `→`, `|`, `—` | Reads symbol names or garbles | Use "to", a comma, or a natural pause |
| `~~strikethrough~~` | Reads "tilde tilde" | Rephrase without strikethrough |
| `> blockquote` | Reads "greater than" | Just say the quoted text |

## Rule

1. **Before writing any speak string for `oc-speak.sh`**, mentally read it as a TTS engine would. If any character would be spoken as its symbol name (asterisk, hash, backtick, tilde, pipe, bracket, etc.), remove it or rewrite the phrase.
2. **No markdown formatting of any kind** — not bold, not italic, not headings, not lists, not links, not code spans.
3. **No raw variable names or code syntax** — say "the speak script" not "friday-speak.py", say "the ambient gap setting" not "FRIDAY_AMBIENT_POST_TTS_GAP".
4. **No special Unicode symbols** — no arrows, no box-drawing, no emoji, no decorative punctuation.
5. Numbers, units, and percentages must be spelled out as words: "twelve seconds" not "12s", "five percent" not "5%".

## Quick self-check

If your TTS string contains any of these characters, it is wrong:

```
* _ ` # ~ | > [ ] ( ) { } → ← — % $
```

Rewrite until the string contains only letters, commas, periods, question marks, exclamation marks, apostrophes, hyphens (in compound words), and spaces.

## Applies to

- Acknowledgement lines ("Got it. ...")
- Thinking narration (thinking mode via `oc-speak.sh`)
- Phase narration (thinking sounds)
- Completion summaries ("Done. ...")
- Questions spoken aloud
- Subagent TTS (all session types)
- Any other invocation of `oc-speak.sh`
